      • reloadExecutors

        protected void reloadExecutors(java.io.File file,
                               java.io.FileFilter filter)
                        throws javax.script.ScriptException,
                               java.io.IOException
        Loads all the Executor files and files under the folders. If Executors are inside the folder, the folder name will be added infront of them. For example, an Executor named test is under folder named hi, then its name will be hi:test; therefore, you should #hi:test to call this executor.
        Parameters:
        file - the target file/folder
        filter - the filter for Executors. Usually you check if the file ends withd .js or is a folder.
        Throws:
        javax.script.ScriptException
        java.io.IOException

      • extractCustomVariables

        protected abstract void extractCustomVariables(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> variables,
                                               java.lang.Object e)
        Extract and put necessary variables needed for the Executors to work properly. For Bukkit API for example, you will have to extract 'player' variable manually for inventory events as Player instance is not saved in the field of Inventory evnet classes.
        Parameters:
        variables - the local variable map.
        e - the context.
